history.content: Data 8 is not a programming course but is rather an introduction to data science and statistical techniques. Having taken 61A, you should have no problem in the coding portion of the class but the concepts will obviously be new and useful to you.

children.subject: People who didn’t take data 8 usually have a little harder time

I'm currently taking Data 100 without having taken Data 8 in the past and am doing well. You might be at a bit of a disadvantage concept-wise compared to students who have taken Data 8, but I don't think it's difficult to catch up and is definitely doable.

history.content:
Hello! I've been hearing a lot of mixed comments about whether there is a point in taking Data 8 after CS 61A, and so I was just wondering could those who've taken both classes shed some light on how useful it is to take Data 8 after 61A?

*EDIT Could I, for instance, take DATA 100 straight without taking DATA 8?
